          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The diameter of the gamma beam at the  place  of  the",
                " targets  was  35 mm.  The doses of gamma-irradiation",
                " were 3690 roentgen for Ca and 6027 roentgen for K."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A cylinder  of natural Ca (hight = 20 mm,  diameter =",
                " 29 mm,  weght = 19 g)  and  a  spherical  target  of",
                " natural K (diameter = 30 mm, weght = 12 g)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLATE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ilford L4 emulsion (thickness = 400 mu,  area",
                " = 1 x 3 inches). The nuclear plates were screened by",
                " 3 mm thick Pb foils against the low  energy  photons",
                " diffused by the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A) for the probability of  escape  of  recoil  proton",
                " tracks from the emulsion,",
                "B) for the neutron absorption in the target,  in  the",
                " window  of the vessel containing the K target and in",
                " Pb foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The evaporation theory was used.  The fraction",
                " of neutrons exceeding the theoretical values at high",
                " neutron energies is reported."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The spectra  show  that at least 50%  of the neutrons",
                " above 2 MeV are due to direct process.  For  Ca  and",
                " also  for  K a second resonance seems to exist about",
                " 10 MeV above the threshold.  At 31 MeV  photoneutron",
                " yields  for Ca and K at angle = 90 degrees for E > 2",
                " MeV are about the same."
              ]
            }
          ],
